{
  "name": "redeem_drains_backlog_to_zero_v32",
  "description": "Synthetic repro of Sepolia block 100,435,687: a retryable submit grows the L2 gas backlog to a non-zero value, then a redeem with gas_to_donate matching the backlog drains it to zero (new_backlog == 0), exercising the EIP-2200 SSTORE_RESET write-cost branch in legacy_actual_backlog_cost. At ArbOS v32 this is the bug fixed by commit 7884d44 — pre-fix arbreth charged SSTORE_GAS (20000) for the write instead of SSTORE_RESET_GAS (5000), overcharging redeem by 15000 gas. The submit message must produce a backlog growth such that the subsequent redeem's gas_to_donate is exactly equal to the resulting backlog. See arb-precompiles/src/arbretryabletx.rs::legacy_actual_backlog_cost.",
